Here's the complete implementation:

**Configure request size limits in `Program.cs`:**

```csharp
// Raise Kestrel's max request body size (default is ~28MB, but be explicit)
builder.WebHost.ConfigureKestrel(o => o.Limits.MaxRequestBodySize = 11 * 1024 * 1024);

// If behind IIS, also raise its limit
builder.Services.Configure<IISServerOptions>(o => o.MaxRequestBodySize = 11 * 1024 * 1024);
```

**Add the endpoint after `app.UseAntiforgery()`:**

```csharp
app.MapPost("/upload", async (IFormFile file) =>
{
    // Validate content type
    string[] allowed = ["image/jpeg", "image/png"];
    if (!allowed.Contains(file.ContentType))
        return Results.BadRequest("Only JPEG and PNG files are allowed.");

    // Validate size (10 MB)
    const long maxSize = 10 * 1024 * 1024;
    if (file.Length > maxSize)
        return Results.BadRequest("File must be 10 MB or smaller.");

    // Build a safe file name to avoid path traversal
    var ext = Path.GetExtension(file.FileName).ToLowerInvariant();
    if (ext is not ".jpg" and not ".jpeg" and not ".png")
        return Results.BadRequest("Invalid file extension.");

    var uploadsDir = Path.Combine(Directory.GetCurrentDirectory(), "uploads");
    Directory.CreateDirectory(uploadsDir);

    var savedName = $"{Guid.NewGuid()}{ext}";
    var filePath = Path.Combine(uploadsDir, savedName);

    await using var stream = new FileStream(filePath, FileMode.Create);
    await file.CopyToAsync(stream);

    return Results.Ok(new { fileName = savedName });
})
.DisableAntiforgery()   // file uploads from API clients; remove if using Razor forms
.DisableRequestSizeLimit(); // let our own 10 MB check handle it instead of 415s
```

**Key points:**

- **`IFormFile` binding** — the framework reads `multipart/form-data` automatically.
- **Double validation** — both `ContentType` and file extension are checked (content type is caller-supplied, so extension adds a second gate).
- **`Guid` file name** — prevents path traversal and collisions.
- **`.DisableAntiforgery()`** — needed for non-browser API clients. Remove this if your consumers are Razor forms that send the antiforgery token.
- **`.DisableRequestSizeLimit()`** — optional; removes the per-endpoint Kestrel limit so your own 10 MB logic is the single source of truth. Alternatively, use `.RequestSizeLimit(11 * 1024 * 1024)` to keep a hard ceiling.

For production, consider also validating the file's [magic bytes](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_file_signatures) (e.g. `FF D8 FF` for JPEG, `89 50 4E 47` for PNG) to guard against spoofed content types.
